<strong>Additions:</strong><br />
<span class="additions">If you just need to use the DES for TRE overflow, this is handled automatically when you write in 2.0.  Additionally, if you are reading data into a Record and data shows up in the DES, you can use the Record's merge() function to resort overflow data into its appropriate subheader (image, for instance).</span><br /><br />
